^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|3N bid was excellent. kia  was lucky the diamond suit was distributed such that it makes, but there are many hands I could have where 3N is cold. Even if I don't have the K of clubs, his hand is worth six club tricks at least, and 7 if the finesse works. So although he ostensibly only has 9 HCP, he has a very powerful hand. If you use Bergen Starting Points he has 9 HCP + 3 length points + 1 quality suit - 1 dubious doubleton = 13. So his hand is very good. It is certainly possible that 5@C makes and 3N doesn't. But, in general, a nine trick contract is usually more likely to make than an 11 trick contract.|
