^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|I was asked why I did not open 1@S.  I am of the school that believes with 15-17 balanced, opening 1N is better even with a 5 card major. There are 2 reasons for my belief. One is, it is awkward to bid a 15-17 hand, after opening 1@S. Suppose kia bids 1N forcing, very likely. Then do I bid 2N? So opening 1N is more descriptive. You very rarely end up in the wrong contract. The only time is when kia has exactly 3 spades, and we cant make 3N and can make 4@S. But that rarely happens in real life.|
