^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|OK, let's finish our defensive discussion first. I made an unfortunate lead. This gets back to the issue of passive vs. aggressive defense.  pam knows after the first trick that clubs are set up. So she needs to be worried, given dee bid spades and diamonds, that we may end up losing a heart trick. If pam had the ace of hearts, it would be much harder to lead a heart. But since she does not, leading a heart will not cost a trick, since dee can always lead a heart to the king herself.|
